---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Mail } from 'lucide-astro';

const title = 'Partners - RCC-GIS';
const description = 'Learn about our faculty, research, and service-focused partners at the University of Chicago';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-4xl">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Our Partners</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground">Collaborating to advance geospatial research and services at the University of Chicago</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg mx-auto">
      <p class="text-lg mb-8">
        The RCC-GIS collaborates with various faculty, research, and service-focused partners at the University of Chicago to enhance geospatial research, innovation, and operational support. These partnerships are essential for advancing interdisciplinary research, providing access to specialized resources, and fostering collaboration among researchers and service providers.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-12">
        <!-- CAMEL Lab -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">CAMEL Lab: Center for Ancient Middle Eastern Landscapes</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            The CAMEL Lab focuses on archaeological research using GIS and remote sensing technologies. RCC-GIS partners with CAMEL to provide technical support and resources for faculty conducting research on ancient landscapes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- CSDS -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">CSDS: Center for Spatial Data Science</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            The Center for Spatial Data Science (CSDS) is dedicated to advancing spatial analysis methods and tools. It collaborates with RCC-GIS to support faculty research initiatives and promote interdisciplinary projects that leverage geospatial data.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Library GIS -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">Library GIS</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            The University of Chicago Library GIS team collaborates with RCC-GIS to provide geospatial resources, data, and training to faculty, researchers, and students, ensuring access to cutting-edge tools and datasets.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Mansueto Institute -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">Mansueto Institute for Urban Innovation</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            The Mansueto Institute collaborates with RCC-GIS to address urban challenges through data-driven research. This partnership supports faculty in exploring topics such as urbanization, sustainability, and social equity using geospatial analysis.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- RDCEP -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">RDCEP: Robust Decision-making on Climate and Energy Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            RDCEP utilizes GIS to analyze the impacts of climate and energy policies. RCC-GIS provides essential geospatial tools and expertise to faculty involved in this critical research area.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- UChicago Justice Project -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">UChicago Justice Project</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            The UChicago Justice Project employs GIS to investigate spatial patterns in crime and justice. RCC-GIS collaborates with faculty on research initiatives that aim to understand and address social inequalities through spatial analysis.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Urban Lab -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">Urban Lab</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            The Urban Lab focuses on urban development, policy, and sustainability. RCC-GIS supports the lab by providing geospatial tools and expertise to analyze urban systems and inform policy decisions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Committee on Environment, Geography, and Urbanization -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">Committee on Environment, Geography, and Urbanization</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            This committee fosters interdisciplinary research on environmental and urban challenges. RCC-GIS collaborates with the committee to integrate GIS into research and teaching, supporting both faculty and students.
          </p>
        </div>


        <!-- Digital Forum for Humanities -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">Digital Forum for Humanities</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            The Digital Forum for Humanities integrates GIS into humanities research, enabling faculty to explore spatial narratives and historical geographies. RCC-GIS provides technical support and training for these projects.
          </p>
        </div>


        <!-- Facilities Services of UChicago and UCMC -->
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">Facilities Services of UChicago and UCMC</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Facilities Services at UChicago and the University of Chicago Medical Center (UCMC) use GIS to manage campus infrastructure and planning. RCC-GIS supports these efforts by providing geospatial expertise and tools for operational efficiency.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>


    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
